{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/85558", "id": 650156032, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NjUwMTU2MDMy", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/85558", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/85558.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/85558.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/85558", "number": 85558, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Diverging tyvars", "user": {"login": "lovishpuri", "id": 11277247, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExMjc3MjQ3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/11277247?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri", "html_url": "https://github.com/lovishpuri", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lovishpuri/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Rebased with master and resolved conflicts.\r\n\r\n\r\n-- Copied from #85021 --\r\nPreviously, the never type will be replaced by a diverging type variable (generally) only if some coercion occurs. It can cause inconsistent behaviors like\r\n```rust\r\nreturn.foo();      //~ ERROR no method named `foo` found for type `!`\r\n{ return }.foo();  //~ ERROR type annotations needed\r\n```\r\n```rust\r\nlet a = (return, );          // The type is `(!, )`.\r\nlet a = ({ return }, );      // The type is `(_, )`.\r\nlet a: (_, ) = (return, );   // The type is `(_, )`.\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith the first commit, the never type will be replaced by a diverging type variable just at the end of the type check for every expression, even if no coercion occurs. Thus the problems above get solved and the consistency should be improved.\r\n\r\nThen, another problem is we'll issue too many \"type annotations needed\". They are issued when types must be known at some point but the resolution failed, even if the type variables are just some diverging ones. A typical example is `{ return }.foo()`.\r\n\r\nWith the second commit, the information about diverging is recorded in the unification table, so that we can check whether performing the fallback affects other non-diverging type variables. If it doesn't, we will safely perform the fallback and we won't issue \"type annotations needed\" anymore.\r\n\r\nAs a result, \"type annotations needed\" will be issued for\r\n```rust\r\nlet a = return;\r\n{ if true { a } else { return } }.foo();\r\n```\r\nbut not for\r\n```rust\r\nlet a: ! = return;\r\n{ if true { a } else { return } }.foo();\r\n```\r\n\r\nDiscussed at https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/259160-t-lang.2Fproject-never-type/topic/Never.20type.20in.20tuple .", "created_at": "2021-05-21T17:17:05Z", "updated_at": "2022-01-30T04:50:56Z", "closed_at": "2022-01-30T04:50:54Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "63ba22a53a315559153a997c5f7365aad6d8d1ba", "assignee": {"login": "nikomatsakis", "id": 155238, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1NTIzOA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/155238?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis", "html_url": "https://github.com/nikomatsakis", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/starr